Must be the lawyer in me, but I don't like the internal inconsistency. i.e. the document purports to follow laws, but the addition of new terms to a concluded contract can never be lawfully enforced or contractually effective, unless there is agreement between the parties on a variety of matters (e.g. the terms, the price, etc).

It might work better if the subsequent terms offered something even more desirable, in return for a more horrible price. The contract would be become effective either by signature or by mental consent.







